Description: The label shows two types of data, namely, days since last UAR and last UAR date.  Days since last UAR is calculated by UI based on last_uar_date provided in the xml.

The value in curr_job_oe_auth_role_id (btfg$code_ui_auth_role) is provided below.  ID INTL_ID USER_ID Name 1 btfg$can_tran BTFG$CAN_TRAN Can transact 2 btft$can_updt BTFG$CAN_UPDT Can update 3 btfg$can_not_tran BTFG$CAN_NOT_TRAN Cannot transact cash 4 btfg$read_only BTFG$READ_ONLY Read only  In one of the following cases, the data source is the xpath shown on the left column: 1. Successful navigation to the UAR page, 2. Successful submission of request to Avaloq (However, the underlying jobs in the request can be successfully or unsuccessfully processed.), or 3. Confirmed request to “Cancel and revert all”.  Where a UAR authoriser has modified the permission of a job in current session and has not submitted any request to update and has not made any request to “Cancel and revert all”, the permission shown here is the one entered by the UAR authoriser in the “Manage permissions for this role” modal.   Note that where a new permission is selected by a UAR authoriser in the “Manage permissions for this role” modal, in the submit request the new permission is passed to the service via • data/uar_lists/dir_job_list/uar_rec/job_oe_auth_role_id or • data/uar_lists/indir_job_list/uar_rec/job_oe_auth_role_id. In the submit request, decsn_id and job_oe_auth_role_id go hand-in-hand. If decsn_id is provided, job_oe_auth_role_id must be provided. Otherwise, job_oe_auth_role_id must be null. Please refer to the IFS for a xml sample on this.

“s#err.10050” is returned by Avaloq when the Notice Period cannot be applied as maturity is in 32 days or less.  If a term deposit cannot be broken from Notice Period and maturity date perspective, error message “s#err.10050” will appear in the path: fidd:fidd_rsp/rsp/valid/err_list/err/err_msg  Otherwise (i.e. the term deposit can be broken), the “s#err.10050” error message will not be returned by Avaloq.  Note that it is possible to have other error message(s) in the error list. At the moment, they are all technical errors, if any. There is not any other business scenario error (other than 10050). The technical errors are to be handled by the standard way.
adjust_widrw_intr_rate is in %. For example, value 2.15 means 2.15%.
The Recommended review date is 28 days from the UAR date.

As the business sets up discount for SMSF administration fee as a percentage, the spcd_offset_val_type_id will be 9. The details of the code is available in Btfg$cost_ovr_type (cached table)  ID INTL_ID USER_ID NAME 9 spcd_perc_disc SPCD_PERC_DISC Discount in %  Appendix A (Avaloq Fee Concept) provides an explanation of how the special condition codes work. It is intended for general knowledge only. The steps describe below has already taken into account how the business intends to use the system and is sufficient for the current UI build.  Use the following steps to calculate the SMSF administration fee net of discount. 1. For each btfg_book_kind_id (i.e. component) of the SMSF administration fee where spcd_offset_val_type_id is equal to 9, calculate net fee amount of the component = tariff_amt * (1 – (spcd_offset_val / 100)) 2. The net fee amount of each component (i.e. each of the amount calculated in first step) of SMSF administration fee  is rounded up to 2 decimal places. 3. Sum up the amount calculated in second step  Btfg$book_kind (cached table) for SMSF administration fee are provided below. This is for information only. The UI should not worry about what btfg_book_kind_id is.  ID INTL_ID USER_ID NAME 544 btfg$smsf_fd_admin_fee SMSF_FD_ADMIN_FEE SMSF Administration fee 555 btfg$smsf_fd_admin_fee_dg SMSF_FD_ADMIN_FEE_DG SMSF Administration fee DG

The existence of tariff_bnd_list path of a btfg$book_kind_id indicates that the fee is a sliding scale fee for the btfg$book_kind_id.  For each book kind, the tariff_factor and tariff_bnd_list are mutually exclusive.

Fixed % fee rate, e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%.  For display purpose, the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example, it will be 2.57%.  In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio, it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). Hence this element is added up for the same portfolio and same master book kind and then rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.  In the case of a portfolio management fee, it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However, the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.

This element shows the underlying components (cost profile) of a fee.  The underlying components of an investment management fee of a portfolio can have multiple components which are listed below. (Btfg$book_kind cached table)  USER_ID INTL_ID NAME TMP_MNGT btfg$tmp_mngt Portfolio management fee

Fixed % fee rate, e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%. For display purpose, the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example, it will be 2.57%. In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio, it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). Hence this element is added up for the same portfolio and same master book kind and then rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI. In the case of a portfolio management fee, it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However, the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.
